<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3769&amp;p=29407#p29407"><![CDATA[
Nesticle was good for its time but sucks now.<br /><br />I second dXtr's motion to try your screen mock-ups on an emulator that performs NTSC simulation, such as Nestopia. Also remember that pixels on an NES connected to a TV are not square; instead, NTSC NES images are stretched horizontally by a factor very close to 8/7, which Nintendulator did not emulate last time I checked.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Dec 12, 2007 3:09 pm</p><hr />
